						<summary>

						<p>The inscription belongs to king <hi rend="bold">Bhuvanaikamalladēva (Sōmēśvara II)</hi> and is very much damaged and mutilated. It seems to refer to a subordinate of the king, who bore among other titles the epithet <hi rend="italic">‘Saṅgrāma-Garuḍa’ i.e.,</hi> a ‘Garuḍa in battle.’</p>						

						</summary>
